All Known Implementing Classes:
ArrayOpenHashIndexedIntSet, BlockOpenHashIndexedIntSet
public interface IndexedIntSet
extends IndexedSet<java.lang.Integer>, IndexedIntCollection

A searchable indexed collection, that contains no duplicate elements..

An indexed set of integers, that associates with each unique integer (element, or key) inserted in the set a unique identifier (index), in an injective mapping: given an element value present in the set, the associated index can be obtained, and conversely, given a valid index, the associated element can be retrieved or removed.

static interface IndexedIntSet.IntEntry
          A generic Entry for an IndexedSet.

This interface materializes the association between an element contained in the set, and its unique identifier.
